The other part wants me to keep it as my dirty little secret, as I feel I should already be established. 

I just want my boys to be proud and remember the day I showed them my acceptance letter. I want them to know it’s ok to not have it all together when you’re 18 and starting over isn’t a sign of weakness. 

Red is rad. Blue will be rad soon, I hope.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/0Za6RDF</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[synonymswirl]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Yep</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/aKEo4BK</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/FsYH4QH.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/aKEo4BK</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Ultraruben]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>No Justice, No Peace</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/kXB0gl8</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/9fPhAwh.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/kXB0gl8</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[WeDontNeedNoStinkingAdvertisements]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Platypus is excellent</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Jt1plqn</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/iQIo1VR.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>this is not Platypus.  This is a stone.  Moving on.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/AgnLEDb.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is Penny the Platypus.  She is excellent !  She came out an egg which was laid in an underground borrow.  Platypus is one of only two mammals that lay eggs.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/EJKYpgl.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Phoebe the Platypus looks all cute because Platypus is all cute.  However these back legs have a sneaky feature.  The claws produce venom!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/TfONd31.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is Pinocchio the Platypus.  His quacker has no teeth inside and it feels rubbery to touch.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/0Fu5CX0.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Meaning this man is a bit of a wimp 'caus the bite of Pumpkin the Platypus doesn't hurt much.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/gOBIRss.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is Princess Poppy the Platypus.  She has a built in electro sensory system for finding food under water.  She enjoys insect larvae, hawaiian pizza, freshwater shrimps, and crayfish.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/nPia3xO.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Porker the Platypus has webbed feet to help him swim.  The same as a water bird has.  He can retract the webbed feet and expose his nails, allowing him to run on land.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/7J5W6dR.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Here's Pup Tart the Platypus.  His fur is super thick to help him keep warm.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/4ry4loo.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Peanut the Platypus has foldable covers for his eyes and ears as well as watertight nostrils.  He swims with them shut and relies on his built in sensory system to navigate and hunt.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Eq35mK0.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Here's Periwinkle the Platypus.  He is excellent.

Brother from another mother:
